---
title: Grids
---


<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h1>Grid System</h1>
    <p>Buoy uses standard Foundation grids with a 12 column layout, with a baseline font-size of 16px. The body measure is 1000px and the gutter size is 1.5em (equivalent to 24px).</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-4 show-grid">
  <div class="small-2 columns"><span>.small-2 columns</span></div>
  <div class="small-2 columns"><span>.small-2 columns</span></div>
  <div class="small-2 columns"><span>.small-2 columns</span></div>
  <div class="small-2 columns"><span>.small-2 columns</span></div>
  <div class="small-2 columns"><span>.small-2 columns</span></div>
  <div class="small-2 columns"><span>.small-2 columns</span></div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-4 show-grid">
  <div class="small-3 columns"><span>.small-3 columns</span></div>
  <div class="small-3 columns"><span>.small-3 columns</span></div>
  <div class="small-3 columns"><span>.small-3 columns</span></div>
  <div class="small-3 columns"><span>.small-3 columns</span></div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-4 show-grid">
  <div class="small-4 columns"><span>.small-4 columns</span></div>
  <div class="small-4 columns"><span>.small-4 columns</span></div>
  <div class="small-4 columns"><span>.small-4 columns</span></div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-4 show-grid">
  <div class="small-6 columns"><span>.small-6 columns</span></div>
  <div class="small-6 columns"><span>.small-6 columns</span></div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-7 show-grid">
  <div class="small-12 columns"><span>.small-12 columns</span></div>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h2>Basic Use</h2>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <p>The Foundation grid is easy to use. Simply add some basic classes to your markup.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Give each horizontal row a wrapper with a class of <code>.row</code>.</li>
      <li>Wrap each column with a class of <code>.columns</code> and <code>.small-{number of columns}</code>.</li>
      <li>Columns should add up to 12, unless you're doing something weird.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="example">
    <div class="row show-grid">
      <div class="small-3 columns"><span>.small-3 columns</span></div>
      <div class="small-3 columns"><span>.small-3 columns</span></div>
      <div class="small-6 columns"><span>.small-6 columns</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <pre>
    <code><%= display_code('
<div class="row">
  <div class="small-3 columns">...</div>
  <div class="small-3 columns">...</div>
  <div class="small-6 columns">...</div>
</div>') %></code>
  </pre>
</div>



<div class="row">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h2>Nesting</h2>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <p>We can nest additional grid systems within a particular column by adding additional rows within any block.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="example">
    <div class="row show-grid">
      <div class="small-3 columns"><span>small-3 columns</span></div>
      <div class="small-6 columns">
        <span>
         <div class="row show-grid">
           <div class="small-3 columns"><span>...</span></div> 
           <div class="small-9 columns"><span>small-9 columns</span></div> 
         </div>
       </span>
      </div>
      <div class="small-3 columns"><span>small-3 columns</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <pre>
    <code><%= display_code('
<div class="row">
  <div class="small-3 columns">...</div>
  <div class="small-9 columns">
     <div class="row">
       <div class="small-3 columns">...</div> 
       <div class="small-9 columns">...</div> 
     </div>
  </div>
  <div class="small-3 columns">...</div>
</div>') %></code>
  </pre>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h2>Advanced</h2>
    <h3>Force block not to float right</h3>
    <p>By default, if you have less than 12 columns in a row, the last block floats to the right edge of the grid. In order to keep it flush against previous blocks, add a class of <code>.end</code>.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="example">
    <div class="row show-grid">
      <div class="small-4 columns"><span>small-3 columns</span></div>
      <div class="small-3 columns end"><span>small-3 columns</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <pre>
    <code><%= display_code('
<div class="row">
  <div class="small-4 columns"></div>
  <div class="small-3 columns end"></div>
</div>') %></code>
  </pre>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h3>Remove column gutters (remove all built-in padding)</h3>
    <p>Add a class of <code>.small-collapse</code> to any row and it will remove padding.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="example">
    <div class="row show-grid small-collapse">
      <div class="small-4 columns"><span>small-4 columns</span></div>
      <div class="small-4 columns"><span>small-4 columns</span></div>
      <div class="small-4 columns"><span>small-4 columns</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <pre>
    <code><%= display_code('
<div class="row small-collapse">
  <div class="small-4 columns"></div>
  <div class="small-4 columns"></div>
  <div class="small-4 columns"></div>
</div>') %></code>
  </pre>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h3>Center Columns</h3>
    <p>We can center a column in a row by adding a class of <code>.small-centered</code> to a column.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="example">
    <div class="row show-grid">
      <div class="small-6 columns small-centered"><span>small-6 columns small-centered</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <pre>
    <code><%= display_code('
<div class="row">
  <div class="small-6 columns small-centered"></div>
</div>') %></code>
  </pre>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h3>Offset</h3>
    <p>We can move blocks x columns to the right by adding a class of <code>.small-offset-{# blocks to offset}</code>.</p>
  </div>
</div>


<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="example">
    <div class="row show-grid">
      <div class="small-6 columns small-offset-2"><span>small-6 columns small-offset-2</span></div>
      <div class="small-2 columns"><span>...</span></div>
      <div class="small-2 columns"><span>...</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <pre>
    <code><%= display_code('
<div class="row">
  <div class="small-6 columns small-offset-2"></div>
  <div class="small-2 columns"></div>
  <div class="small-2 columns"></div>
</div>') %></code>
  </pre>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h3>Pushing and Pulling Columns</h3>
    <p>We can very easily move a block x cells left or right by pushing and pulling. Pushing or pulling a column does not effect adjacent columns.</p>

    <p>For example, to push a block 2 columns to the right we add a class of: <code>.small-push-2</code>. To pull a block 2 columns to the left we add a class of: <code>.small-pull-2</code>.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="example">
    <div class="row show-grid">
      <div class="small-6 columns small-push-2"><span>small-6 columns small-push-2</span></div>
      <div class="small-2 columns"><span>...</span></div>
      <div class="small-2 columns"><span>...</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <pre>
    <code><%= display_code('
<div class="row">
  <div class="small-6 columns small-push-2"></div>
  <div class="small-2 columns"></div>
  <div class="small-2 columns"></div>
</div>') %></code>
  </pre>
</div>